%N A395225 Denominator of (zeta(4*n) / zeta(2*n)^2) * (4^n + 1)/(4^n - 1) for n >= 1.
%C A395225 This sequence is the denominator analog of A395224 and can be viewed as a variation of A114362/A114363, removing the contribution of the prime p=2 from the Euler product.
%F A395225 a(n) = denominator( ((2 * abs(bernoulli(4*n)) * ((2*n)!)^2) / (bernoulli(2*n)^2 * (4*n)!)) * (4^n + 1) / (4^n - 1) ).
%F A395225 a(n) = denominator( (zeta(4*n)/zeta(2*n)^2) * (2^(4*n) + 2^(2*n)) / (2^(4*n) - 2^(2*n)) ).
%F A395225 a(n) = denominator(Product_{p prime > 2} (p^(2*n) - 1) / (p^(2*n) + 1)).
%e A395225 For n = 2: (zeta(8)/zeta(4)^2) * (4^2 + 1)/(4^2 - 1) = ((Pi^8/9450) / (Pi^4/90)^2) * (17/15) = (6/7) * (17/15) = 102/105 = 34/35. The denominator is 35.
%e A395225 For n = 3: (zeta(12)/zeta(6)^2) * (4^3 + 1)/(4^3 - 1) = ((691*Pi^12/638512875) / (Pi^6/945)^2) * (65/63) = (691/715) * (65/63) = 691/693. The denominator is 693.
%o A395225 (PARI) {a(n) = denominator((2*abs(bernfrac(4*n))*(2*n)!^2) / (bernfrac(2*n)^2*(4*n)!) * (4^n+1)/(4^n-1))}
%Y A395225 Cf. A395224 (numerators), A000367, A002445 (Bernoulli numbers), A046988, A002432, A114362, A114363.
%K A395225 nonn,frac,new
%O A395225 1,1
%A A395225 _Dimitris Valianatos_, Apr 16 2026
